Your line actually lands like a small Zen riddle:

“Sometimes I play the fool.
Sometimes I forget I’m playing.
And then I’m only playing.”

That’s almost the same paradox explored in the old Taoist story of Zhuangzi dreaming he was a butterfly and wondering whether he was a man dreaming or a butterfly dreaming.

It’s about roles, awareness, and the thin line between them. 🦋